# AI Agent Playbook (Excalidraw monorepo)

Primary command menu lives in `.cursor/commands/COMMANDS.md` (keep this rule short and stable).

## Default workflow commands

- **Install**: Prefer `yarn` (repo uses `yarn@1.22.22`).
  - `yarn install`
  - If install issues: `yarn clean-install`
- **Dev (app)**: `yarn start` (runs `./excalidraw-app start`)
- **Build (app)**: `yarn build`
- **Build (packages)**: `yarn build:packages`
- **Tests**:
  - App/unit: `yarn test` (vitest)
  - Full suite: `yarn test:all`
  - Typecheck: `yarn test:typecheck`
  - Lint: `yarn test:code`
  - Prettier check: `yarn test:other`
- **Auto-fix**:
  - Prettier write: `yarn fix:other`
  - ESLint fix: `yarn fix:code`
  - Both: `yarn fix`

## Repo navigation hints

- **App**: `excalidraw-app/`
- **Packages**: `packages/*`
- **Examples**: `examples/*`
- **Scripts**: `scripts/`
- **Docs**: `dev-docs/` and root `README.md`

## Safety & hygiene rules

- **No secrets**: never commit `.env*`, keys, tokens, credentials.
- **No destructive git**: avoid force-push / hard reset unless explicitly requested.
- **Prefer minimal diffs**: keep changes scoped to the user’s request; don’t reformat unrelated files.
- **Respect tooling**: keep `yarn.lock` consistent with changes; only change dependencies when needed.

## How to respond (style)

- Ask only when blocked; otherwise make reasonable defaults and proceed.
- When adding new code, also add/update the nearest tests if the repo already has tests for that area.
